"This guide forms part of the Privacy Policy upon which the additional clarification and guidance on the minors' personal information requiring strengthened protection is also builds. We will undertake to explain to the guardians (hereinafter referred to as you) and children (hereinafter referred to as the minors) how we collect, use, store, and process minors' personal information, and provide guidance on how to access, correct, delete, and protect such information in accordance with this guide. In the event of any inconsistency with the Privacy Policy in the protection of minors personal information, this guide shall prevail."

"It should be understood that this guide applies only to our products or services specifically intended for or possibly involving minors under the age of 14. For products or services that don't identify or actively identify the user's age, the Privacy Policy shall apply. Provisions that are or may be materially related to the rights and interests of children have been rendered in bold to draw attention and for greater ease of understanding."

"We collect only that information necessary to achieve the functions of the products listed below in accordance with the laws and regulations and the agreement with you, based on the principles of legality, legitimacy, and necessity. In the course of a minor's use of our products and services, we may ask you to provide the necessary information, as described in the section I. How we collect and use your personal information of our Privacy Policy."

"(1) We may share a minor's personal information with a guardian only with the guardian's prior consent and if the guardian has satisfied the relevant compliance measures required by the \"Personal Information Protection Law of the People's Republic of China\" and other laws and regulations. For example, we may share some of a minor's personal information (such as the minor's user name, account number, or payment history for some of our products and services) with a guardian, who may access and manage the relevant personal information."

(2) We may disclose information about children when required to do so by law, regulation, mandatory administrative enforcement, or judicial request. Subject to laws and regulations, when we receive a request for disclosure of information as described above, we will require the recipient to produce the appropriate legal documents (such as a subpoena or letter of inquiry) in connection with it.

"(3) As our business continues to grow, should a merger, acquisition, asset transfer, or other transaction occur that would result in the sharing or transfer of guardians or children's personal information to a third party, we shall inform the guardians and children of the circumstances through push notifications, announcements, etc., and continue to protect or require the new administrators to continue to protect guardians and children's personal information in accordance with laws and regulations and standards no less stringent than those required by this statement."

(4) In the interests of educating and enhancing the awareness and ability of children to protect their own personal information and to protect the security thereof, we strongly recommend that the functions described in section (1) of this chapter be carried out by a guardian and ask that you carefully consider whether to voluntarily disclose such information when using our products and/or services.

"(5) You may delete your child's personal information through the settings in our products and/or services or in accordance with the procedures of our Parental Monitoring System.
